label: LLIN
definition: Whether this bednet is a long-lasting insecticide treated bednet (LLIN).

label: Brand of bednet
definition: Brand of the bednet.

label: Bednet brand determination method
definition: How the brand of the bednet was determined.

label: Time since bednet obtained categorization
definition: Categorization of the time since the bednet was obtained.

label: Time since bednet obtained
definition: Time since bednet was obtained.

label: Bednet source
definition: Where the bednet was obtained.

label: UCC bednet
definition: Whether the bednet was received during the 2020-2021 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC).

label: Bednet cost categorization
definition: Whether the bednet was obtained for free or was paid for.

label: Bednet study timepoint
definition: Cross-sectional surveys were conducted at 12 months and 24 months after LLIN distribution. If you would like to view only data from a particular timepoint for all variables, please make sure to also select that timepoint for 'Household study timepoint' (under 'Household') or 'Study timepoint' (under 'Participant').

label: Study bednet categorization
definition: Whether or not the household had a study bednet (with a unique bednet identifier). If the household had a study bednet, whether the study bednet was used or not.

label: Bednet data collection date
definition: Date when data on the bednet was collected.

label: Bednet observed
definition: Whether this bednet was observed.

label: Bednet label observed
definition: Whether the label on this bednet was observed.

label: Bednet used last night
definition: Whether anyone slept under this bednet last night.

label: Bednet hung categorization
definition: Categorization of whether this bednet was hung.

label: Bednet hung
definition: If this bednet was observed, whether this bednet was hanging at study visit.

label: Bednet ever hung
definition: If this bednet was observed but not hanging at study visit, whether this bednet was ever hung.

label: Non-observed bednet ever hung
definition: If this bednet was not observed at study visit, whether this bednet was ever hung.

label: Baseline malaria incidence per 1000 person years
definition: Baseline malaria incidence per 1000 person-years (3 months pre-intervention).

label: LLIN distribution date
definition: Month and year long-lasting insecticide treated bednets (LLINs) were distributed.

label: Time since LLIN distribution
definition: The amount of time that has elapsed since long-lasting insecticide treated bednets (LLINs) were distributed to each cluster, assessed monthly.

label: Population
definition: The estimated population of the target catchment area per month.

label: Malaria incidence rate per 1000 people
definition: The estimated incidence of malaria in target catchment areas around health facilities per month. Each health facility was the focal point of a cluster.

label: Malaria test positivity rate in target area
definition: Of those suspected of having malaria each month who live within the defined target catchment area, the proportion that tested positive for malaria.

label: Malaria positive in target area count
definition: Of those suspected of having malaria each month and live within the defined target catchment area, the total number that tested positive for malaria. This is the numerator for the 'Malaria test positivity rate in target area' (TPR).

label: Tested for malaria in target area count
definition: Of those suspected of having malaria each month who live within the defined target catchment area, the total number tested for malaria. This is the denominator for the 'Malaria test positivity rate in target area' (TPR).

label: Adjusted malaria positive in target area count
definition: The adjusted number of persons within the target catchment area who tested positive for malaria per month. Adjusted for missing data on village and malaria testing.

label: Malaria test positivity rate
definition: For each health center, the monthly test positivity rate (TPR) is the proportion of visits with a positive malaria test out of all visits where malaria was suspected and a test for malaria was performed.

label: Malaria positive count
definition: For each health center, the total number of visits per month where malaria was suspected and a test for malaria was performed and the malaria test was positive. This is the numerator for the 'Malaria test positivity rate' (TPR).

label: Tested for malaria count
definition: For each health center, the total number of visits per month where malaria was suspected and a test for malaria was performed. This is the denominator for the 'Malaria test positivity rate' (TPR).

label: Malaria suspected visit count
definition: For each health center, the total number of visits per month where malaria was suspected.

label: Malaria suspected visit proportion
definition: For each health center, the proportion of visits per month where malaria was suspected.

label: Tested for malaria by RDT count
definition: For each health center, the total number of visits per month where a rapid diagnostic test (RDT) for malaria was performed.

label: Tested for malaria by RDT proportion
definition: For each health center, the proportion of visits per month where a rapid diagnostic test (RDT) for malaria was performed.

label: Tested for malaria by RDT in target area count
definition: The total number of visits per month where a rapid diagnostic test (RDT) for malaria was performed on persons living within the defined target catchment area.

label: Tested for malaria by RDT in target area proportion
definition: The proportion of visits per month where a rapid diagnostic test (RDT) for malaria was performed on persons living within the defined target catchment area.

label: Tested for malaria proportion
definition: For each health center, the proportion of visits per month where malaria was suspected and a test for malaria was performed.

label: Aggregate date (month and year)
definition: Cluster-level data was aggregated to the first day of the month in which the data was collected.

label: RDT performed
definition: Whether a rapid diagnostic test for malaria was performed.

label: RDT performed if febrile
definition: If the participant was febrile, whether a rapid diagnostic test for malaria was performed.

label: Blood smear performed
definition: Whether a blood smear was performed.

label: Anemia (hemoglobin <11 g/dL)
definition: Whether the participant had anemia, defined as hemoglobin less than 11 g/dL.

label: Anemia (hemoglobin <10 g/dL)
definition: Whether the participant had anemia, defined as hemoglobin less than 10 g/dL.

label: Anemia (hemoglobin <8 g/dL)
definition: Whether the participant had anemia, defined as hemoglobin less than 8 g/dL.

label: Plasmodium, by RDT
definition: Result of the rapid diagnostic test for malaria.

label: Plasmodium, by thick smear microscopy
definition: Whether Plasmodium parasites were detected by thick smear microscopy.

label: Plasmodium falciparum gametocytes, by microscopy
definition: Whether Plasmodium falciparum gametocytes were present.

label: Plasmodium asexual stages, by microscopy result
definition: Plasmodium parasite density.

label: Filter paper barcode
definition: Barcode identifier for filter paper sample.

label: Blood smear barcode
definition: Barcode identifier for blood smear.

label: Cluster study arm
definition: Type of long-lasting insecticide treated bednet (LLIN) each cluster was randomized to receive. Intervention clusters were randomized to receive pyriproxyfen (PPF) LLINs such as Royal Guard nets; control clusters were randomized to receive piperonyl butoxide (PBO) LLINs such as PermaNet 3.0 nets. Health facilities were the focal point of clusters.

label: Intervention time since LLIN distribution
definition: The amount of time that has elapsed since long-lasting insecticide treated bednets (LLINs) were distributed to the PBO LLIN arm vs the PPF LLIN arm, assessed monthly.

label: Intervention total estimated malaria cases
definition: Total number of estimated cases of malaria at each timepoint in the PPO LLIN arm vs the PPF LLIN arm.

label: Intervention target population
definition: The estimated population of the target catchment areas in the PBO LLIN arm vs the PPF LLIN arm, per month.

label: Intervention malaria incidence per 1000 people
definition: The estimated incidence of malaria in target catchment areas in the PBO LLIN arm vs the PPF LLIN arm, per month. Each cluster was weighted based on the target population size. Malaria incidence measures cater for the staggered distribution of LLINs across the sites ("Study arm time since LLIN distribution").
